article.headline: Tennessee Tech 87, SE Missouri State 76
article.story: COOKEVILLE Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Fisher scored 21 points as Tennessee Tech beat SE Missouri 87-76 on Saturday night. Amadi McKenzie scored 11 points and grabbed a career-high 14 rebounds for the Golden Eagles (14-5, 9-2 Ohio Valley). Belton Rivers added 14 points, Milone Clark had 12 and Derek Stribling had 11. Roy Booker led the Redhawks (6-11, 3-8) with 30 points, including 16-of-18 from the free-throw line. Paul Paradoski added 14 points and had six assists, and Eric Jones netted 11 points. A 12-2 run by Tennessee Tech gave the Golden Eagles a 17-point lead with 8:41 left in the game. SE Missouri cut the margin to 77-73 on two free throws by Jones with 3:20 left. The Golden Eagles followed with six unanswered points. SE Missouri's only lead was with 17:06 left in the first half as Roy Booker hit a 3-pointer to put the Redhawks up 8-6.
